full_description:

Speaker:: Jürgen Gmach

Track: PyCon: Programming & Software Engineering
No matter whether you are starting a new job or you want to contribute to an open-source project,
learning a new code base can be intimidating.

This is especially true for code bases with more than one million lines of code.

This talk will show you approaches, techniques and tools on how to master a new code base.


Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022.
https://2022.pycon.de
More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/WHVGAX
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
